sql:
SELECT name 
FROM power_plants 
WHERE capacity = (SELECT MAX(capacity) FROM power_plants);

external_knowledge:
- The term "operational" refers to power plants that are currently in use and producing energy; 
- "Energy Source" refers to the primary source of energy a power plant uses (e.g., coal, natural gas, biomass); 
- "Technology Type" refers to the method or technology used by the power plant to generate energy (e.g., thermal, renewable, nuclear).

